<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 31 at 4:51AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Light snow through this morning...
A steady light will continue to fall over Central and Southwest MT
through this morning. Visibility will fall to under one mile at
times in areas of heavier snowfall.
New snow accumulations this morning will generally range from
about a half inch to one inch.
Those with travel plans through this morning should be prepared
for snow covered and slippery roadways, along with areas of poor
visibility.</description>
